ce:section.ce:para:
The morphology of the PLA and PLA-CD film surfaces were modified during exposure to the etching process in the oxygen plasma reactor at variable time intervals. These morphologies at the different exposure times are presented in Fig. 4
                           . The roughness of the film surfaces was modified over the measured time intervals (e.g., 0, 3, 5, 7 mins). We observe that the higher plasma exposures time resulted in increase in the surface roughness (Table 2
                           ) for both the PLA and PLA-CD films. This increase was directly proportional to the time of the film exposure to the plasma. The base case roughness without plasma treatment for pure PLA was 15.1 nm, while that for the PLA-CD sample was 18.4 nm. We noted significant increase in roughness of the film surfaces after oxygen plasma treatment. In the case of pure PLA, the roughness was increased to 25.1 nm at 7 min which is about 170% increase compared to pure PLA. Whereas the roughness of PLA-CD film increased to 104.1 nm at 7 min after oxygen plasma treatment, that is, an increase by 570% compared to pure PLA and by 415% compared to PLA-CD.
